Description: Fragment of flattened handle, complete, with neck and shoulder, of a pottery transport amphora; relatively small jar. Clay micaceous fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, worn number, deleted. Name Nikanor. An example in the Benaki collection, Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (345)
